feat(ui): mobile-responsive map & header, global scrollbar hide, manual enterprise login, risk loading fix

Enterprise
- Login page no longer auto-redirects authed visitors; every visit to
  the Enterprise CTA shows the (auto-filled) login form so the user
  must explicitly click "Sign in" before landing on /enterprise/risk-assessment
- /enterprise index now always redirects to /enterprise/login

Risk assessment loading fix
- Add a 6s axios client timeout so failed/unreachable API calls bail
  out quickly instead of hanging the socket for ~30s
- Provide full MOCK_RISK_SCORE + MOCK_FINANCIAL_PROJECTION payloads
  and make getRiskScore / getFinancialProjection fall back to them
  on error — /risk/results now renders even when the backend isn't
  running, fixing the "loading screen stuck" case

Map + street-view responsive
- GooeySearchBar expanded width is now computed at mount time and on
  resize: clamp(220, 92vw, 360) — the search pill fits within the
  map viewport on any phone without losing desktop sizing
- Back-to-globe button already safe-area-aware (kept)

Mobile hamburger stagger
- Wrap the mobile menu panel in AnimatePresence + motion variants
  so each nav row cascades top → bottom when opened (staggerChildren
  0.06, blur+translate per row). Enterprise row participates in the
  same cascade. Uses q-shadow-lux for the menu panel.

Global scrollbar hide
- Hide the native scrollbar on every scrollable surface while
  preserving the scroll interaction (wheel/touch/keyboard). Keeps
  the existing .scrollbar-hide utility for targeted use.

Verified: lints clean, tsc --noEmit clean, next build green (16 routes)
